The Deputy Minister of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Bheki Cele, escaped with minor injuries after being involved in a car accident yesterday afternoon.Cele was travelling with his two security personnel when the vehicle he was travelling in collided with a BMW X5 on the M1 South near the Joe Slovo offramp. His spokesperson, Nonkululeko Phokane, said he was treated at the Milpark Hospital in Johannesburg. They are all fine, he was the only one who sustained injures but they are minor and he is in a stable condition, Phokane said. He has been discharged. The rest of his security team and officials are also fine. The deputy minister was on his way to an appointment with media editors to discuss the road map of his department.THABISO MACHAKA